type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2012-11-06T17:42:40Z","updated_at":"2012-11-06T17:43:00Z","body":"@josevalim yeah, this issue is present. When `current_password` is not valid we call `assign_attributes anyway` which calls `password=` method. Here is a fix:\n\n``` diff\n➜  devise git:(master) ✗ git diff\ndiff --git a/lib/devise/models/database_authenticatable.rb b/lib/devise/models/database_authenticatable.rb\nindex 349147a..a0a0f0d 100644\n--- a/lib/devise/models/database_authenticatable.rb\n+++ b/lib/devise/models/database_authenticatable.rb\n@@ -64,6 +64,7 @@ module Devise\n         result = if valid_password?(current_password)\n           update_attributes(params, *options)\n         else\n+          params.delete(:password)\n           self.assign_attributes(params, *options)\n           self.valid?\n           self.errors.add(:current_password, current_password.blank? ? :blank : :invalid)\ndiff --git a/test/models/database_authenticatable_test.rb b/test/models/database_authenticatable_test.rb\nindex 638eaf3..bacbe98 100644\n--- a/test/models/database_authenticatable_test.rb\n+++ b/test/models/database_authenticatable_test.rb\n@@ -108,6 +108,13 @@ class DatabaseAuthenticatableTest < ActiveSupport::TestCase\n     assert_match \"is invalid\", user.errors[:current_password].join\n   end\n\n+  test 'should not change encrypted password when it is invalid' do\n+    user = create_user\n+    assert_not user.update_with_password(:current_password => 'other',\n+      :password => 'pass4321', :password_confirmation => 'pass4321')\n+    assert_not user.encrypted_password_changed?\n+  end\n+\n   test 'should add an error to current password when it is blank' do\n     user = create_user\n     assert_not user.update_with_password(:password => 'pass4321',\n\n```\n\nwhat do you think?\n","author_association":"COLLABORATOR","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/heartcombo/devise/issues/comments/10119998/reactions","total_count"